<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>The Battle Creek Woman's Temperance Union was established April 13, 1874. In December 1876, the group was formally organized as the Battle Creek Chapter of the Woman's Christian Temperance Union. Due to declining membership, the chapter disbanded November 21, 1986.</p>
</bioghist>



<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The record group documents the local activities of the W.C.T.U .includes minutes of regular meetings (1874-1986, with some gaps), minutes of the Board of Trustees (1907-1975, with some gaps), and minute book of the Red Ribbon Temperance Union, 1880-1882. Also included are record books of the treasurer, yearbooks with lists of officers, a scrapbook and assorted clippings, and reports of the chapter to the Michigan Department of the Treasury.</p>
</scopecontent>

